    <body>
        <h1> Methods in arrays </h1>
        <p>The join method joins the array element into string</p>
        <p>Pop method removes the last element from array</p>
        <div id = "result"></div>
        <div id = "result1"></div>
        <div id = "result2"></div>
        <script>
            fruits = ["apple","mango","banana","kiwi","watermelon"]

            document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = fruits.join("+")  + "<br>"
            fruits.pop()
            document.getElementById("result1").innerHTML = "<br> The first pop " + fruits
            fruits.pop()
            document.getElementById("result2").innerHTML = "<br> The second pop " + fruits
            </script>
            </body>
            </html>